name: Squash Tart
keywords: dessert, dried cranberries, heavy cream, squash, winter
recipeIngredient: 2 cups coarsely grated buttercup or kabocha squash

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine squash, maple syrup or honey, cream, cranberries, ginger, allspice, cloves and salt. Mix thoroughly. Taste, and adjust seasoning, adding more spice if you like. Add eggs, and mix well again so ingredients are completely combined. Pour into prepared tart shell. Set pan on baking sheet on shelf in lower third of oven.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until filling is fully set. Cool completely before cutting.
